[1
Date: Mon, 23 Aug 1999 09:25:01 -0400
From: "MCKINNEY, LUANN(VSD)" <MCKINNEYLTC@nt1.afrri.usuhs.mil>

Why volcano victims [infected?
1) Disrupted sandfly environment: Sandflies normally feed on small rodents
at the forest edge. Disturb or alter the host population on that edge and
the insects seek alternative hosts.
2) Disrupted human environment: Assuming damaged civil infrastructure, or
loss of habitat, more people now in the sandfly environment. Humans become
the alternative host. Also seen when forests are cut down: the small
rodents flee that area where the forest edge used to be. The sandflies then
feed on humans cultivating that zone.
--
LuAnn McKinney, DVM (a onetime Leishmaniac)
Armed Forces Radiobiology Research Institute
Bethesda, MD
<MCKINNEYLTC@nt1.afrri.usuhs.mil>
